On Saturday, nine-year-old Aqeel Davids was gunned down. CAPE TOWN - Gangs shootings again erupted in Ocean View on Monday morning. On Saturday, nine-year-old Aqeel Davids  was gunned down. According to his relatives, a man who was being chased ran into the boy's family house on Saturday night. A gunman then opened fire, hitting the boy. Three other people were wounded during the incident. The Ocean View community policing forum's Kathy Cronje says gang violence flared up on Friday. “Around midnight, a nine-year-old child’s life was taken. On Saturday night it was raining bullets and I believe there are a lot more bullets flying this morning.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)